1. *Kupiš* mi hleb dok ideš u prodavnicu. (Buy me bread while you're going to the store.)
2. Ja obično *kupim* povrće na pijaci. (I usually buy vegetables at the market.)
3. *Kupi* mi jednu limenku piva molim te. (Buy me a can of beer please.)
4. Ako *kupuješ* nove cipele, razmisli o udobnosti pre svega. (If you're buying new shoes, think about comfort above all.)
5. Ona *kupuje* mleko svaki dan. (She buys milk every day.)
6. Da li ćeš *kupiti* kartu za koncert? (Are you going to buy a ticket for the concert?)
7. Moram *kupiti* novu knjigu za kurs srpskog jezika. (I need to buy a new book for my Serbian language course.)
8. *Kupila* je novi telefon jer joj je stari bio previše spor. (She bought a new phone because her old one was too slow.)
9. Ti *kupuješ* previše stvari koje ti nisu potrebne. (You buy too many things that you don't need.)
10. Kada budeš u gradu, *kupi* mi novine. (When you're in town, buy me some newspapers.)